   September 12, 2013
   Hands down the best venue to play a show in DC. It's even great to play
   the backstage, which is ideal for smaller/local bands with less of a
   draw, and you still get treated like royalty with an actual room
   backstage to hang out in, free beer, half off food, a private bathroom
   with a shower, gated parking, storage for gear, and no stairs to climb
   while carrying a 90-lb. bass amp. So many other clubs in DC get this
   wrong and the Black Cat gets it all right. I love you, Black Cat! Don't
   eva change!
